ially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705189,"age":2,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Henry Hambury was born in 1257, in Staffordshire, England, his father, Reginald Hanbury, was 26 and his mother, Joan, was 26. He married Alice Salveyn about 1280, in Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died in 1281, in his hometown, at the age of 24."},"et":{"1257–1281":"1257–1281","1262–1281":"1262–1281","1281–1326":"1281–1326","1232–Male":"1232–Surnud","1232–Female":"1232–Surnud","1326":"1326","about 1280":"umbes 1280","1259":"1259","1257":"1257","1232":"1232","1262":"1262","1281":"1281","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, England"},"fi":{"1257–1281":"1257–1281","1262–1281":"1262–1281","1281–1326":"1281–1326","1232–Male":"1232–Kuollut","1232–Female":"1232–Kuollut","1326":"1326","about 1280":"noin 1280","1259":"1259","1257":"1257","1232":"1232","1262":"1262","1281":"1281","Staffordshire, England":"Staffordshire, England"},"fr":{"1257–1281":"1257–1281","1262–1281":"1262–1281","1281–1326":"1281–1326","1232–Male":"1232–Décédé","1232–Female":"1232–Décédée","1326":"1326","about 1280":"environ 1280","1259":"1259","1257":"1257","1232":"1232","1262":"1262",